# Cursor orchestration (eds-xwalk-ai-agent)

## Skills

- **Read and follow** `.cursor/skills/*/SKILL.md` when the user task matches that skill’s YAML `description` (block workflow, Figma tokens, Admin API, block quality).
- For deeper narrative, use `agent/skills/*.md`, `agent/rules/`, and `agent/validators/`.

## Commands

- Prefer **`.cursor/commands/`** for repeatable HTTP/MCP flows (backend, validate, frontend, figma, admin, `mcp/call`).
- For end-to-end block work, start from **`.cursor/commands/orchestrate-block-xwalk.md`**.

## Sub-agents

- For repo-wide or multi-folder work, **spawn parallel sub-agents** (see root **`AGENTS.md`**) instead of scanning everything serially in one thread.

## Consistency

- **Do not invent UE HTML.** Backend → user UE HTML → frontend.
- **Index-based FE only**; one JS + one CSS per block name.
